checkerProperties.subcategoryLongDescription: Braced-initialization {}, without equals sign, shall be used for variable initialization.

events.covLStrEventDescription: {CovLStrv2{{t{Using basic numerical type {0} rather than a typedef that includes size and signedness information.}{{code{int}}}}}}
events.eventDescription: Using basic numerical type "int" rather than a typedef that includes size and signedness information.

checkerProperties.subcategoryLongDescription: Fixed width integer types from <cstdint>, indicating the size and signedness, shall be used in place of the basic numerical types.
Traditional C-style casts shall not be used.

events.covLStrEventDescription: {CovLStrv2{{t{The variable {0} has a non-const type, however its value is never changed. Consider adding a const qualifier to the variable type.}{{code{a}}}}}}
events.eventDescription: The variable "a" has a non-const type, however its value is never changed. Consider adding a const qualifier to the variable type.

checkerProperties.subcategoryLongDescription: Constexpr or const specifiers shall be used for immutable data declaration.
